General themes in this class 

(A) Modeling high dimensional distributions 
â€¢ Representation: how to represent a family of distributions. ! Examples of convenient
 families are given by graphical models (DGM, UGM). 
â€¢ Parametrization: how to parameterize the members of the family of distributions ! an example for this that we will see is using the exponential family (but there 
are many others) 
(B) Inference ! how do we compute p(xQ | xE), where Q is the query and E the evidence? 
â€¢ Lecture 13 : elimination algorithm 
â€¢ Lecture 14 : sum-product algorithm (belief propagation) 
(C) Statistical estimation: how do we estimate the model from observations? ! Examples 
of principles that we see: maximum likelihood estimators, maximum entropy, method 
of moments 
